text.tspan: In 1995 the average Boston home cost $255,480. In 2025, the average
home now valued at $887,320, a 347% increase over the 30-year period
compared to the 242% increase in median home income over the same
period. On average, prospective home owners in 2025 will expect to pay
30% more on their mortgages than their 1995 counterparts.
Housing is more expensive than ever.
Datasets sourced from FRED Housing and Income Indicies - https://fred.stlouisfred.gov
